Spokane Alliance will build on its current campaign to address budget problems facing the city of Spokane in 2013 and then shift to parallel statewide strategy in 2014.  Its goals are to:
•	develop the citizens vision for the city (Restoring Spokane's Future), 
•	shift the position of council members (a majority of whom currently want to continue slashing services) through district level accountability forums and voter education work, and;
•	secure new budget priorities for the city following the November election. 

For the remainder of 2013, the Sound Alliance will:
•	identify and provide training to a pool of leaders interested in organizing their neighbors;
•	create pilot Neighbors for Good groups in targeted legislative districts through Alliance member organizations;
•	engage Neighbors groups in local campaigns, preferably around issues with the budget impact

Moving into 2014, both Alliances will expand their local organizing/Neighbors for Good strategies to include a wide range of allies.  The focus will shift to: developing a collective vision for the state; popular education about state budgets, revenue options and power dynamics; and developing a policy platform going into the 2014 fall elections.

Quantitatively, the success of the strategy will be measured by the numbers of:
•	leaders who are trained and engage in a campaigns;
•	neighbors for good groups started / people participating;
•	allied groups engaged;
•	local campaign actions carried out; and 
•	people involved in developing a collective vision for the state.

